content:
The `DashboardLayout` component serves as the primary layout structure for the application's dashboard section. It sets up a two-column layout, featuring a `Sidebar` on the left and the main content area on the right.

## Purpose

This layout ensures a consistent navigation and content presentation across all dashboard pages. It provides a fixed sidebar for navigation and a scrollable main content area.

## Key Exports/Functions/Props

*   **`DashboardLayout` (default export)**: A React functional component that accepts `children` as a prop.
    *   `children`: `React.ReactNode` - The content to be rendered within the main area of the dashboard.

## Usage Example

This component is typically used in `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` to wrap the dashboard routes.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/ui/sidebar";

export default function DashboardLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-screen bg-background overflow-hidden">
      <Sidebar />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
```

Any component rendered within the `app/dashboard` directory (e.g., `app/dashboard/page.tsx`) will be rendered as `children` within this layout.
